   "source": [
    ">- The line used to separate the dataset is called a separating hyperplane. \n",
    "-  The points closest to the separating hyperplane are known as support vectors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The distance from a point to the separating plane is given by :\n",
    "$$\\frac{w^Tx+b}{|w|}$$\n",
    "or:\n",
    "$$\\frac{Ax+by+c}{\\sqrt{A^2+B^2}}$$"
   ]
  },
